{"hash":"bab78e1ec5a850f8176b5de9eef2443a64d6d200","data":{"post":{"title":"How to create gitignore file with predefined templates?","content":"<p>For people who create project frequently, one thing that is very annoying would be creating the gitignore file. The same set of files, but why write it again. Even copying from other directory is a waste of effort. This is why I have created <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/gitignorer\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">gitignorer<OutboundLink/></a>.</p>\n<p>To install this program, simply run:</p>\n<!--beforebegin--><div class=\"language- extra-class\"><!--afterbegin--><pre v-pre class=\"language-text\"><code>&gt; npm i -g gitignorer\n</code></pre>\n<!--beforeend--></div><!--afterend--><p>This program allow you to create the gitignore file with a predefined set of files. For example:</p>\n<!--beforebegin--><div class=\"language- extra-class\"><!--afterbegin--><pre v-pre class=\"language-text\"><code>&gt; gitignore init node\n# created by gitignorer\n# profile used: node\n*.sw*\n.DS_Store\nnode_modules\nnpm-debug.log*\n</code></pre>\n<!--beforeend--></div><!--afterend--><p>Isnâ€™t this great?</p>\n<p>All the profiles are defined at <code>~/.gitignore.profiles.js</code>. The definition is simple and intuitive. Here is one of the examples:</p>\n<!--beforebegin--><div class=\"language-javascript extra-class\"><!--afterbegin--><pre v-pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">/*** ~/.gitignore.profiles.js ***/</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> common <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">'*.sw*'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">'.DS_Store'</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n \n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> node <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">'node_modules'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n \n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> java <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">'url: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/github/gitignore/master/Java.gitignore'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">'.object2'</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nmodule<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> common<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  node<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token operator\">...</span>common<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">...</span>node<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  java<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token operator\">...</span>common<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">...</span>java<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  awesome<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token operator\">...</span>commone<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">...</span>node<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">...</span>java<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre>\n<!--beforeend--></div><!--afterend-->"}},"context":{}}